7. Scope Definition 
Document in scope features:
The in-scope features define the functionalities that are included in the Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System.
1.	Incident Reporting: Employees can report security incidents through a web form.
2.	Incident Triage: Security analysts can assess and prioritize incidents.
3.	Incident Assignment: Incidents can be assigned to specific analysts or teams.
4.	Response Workflow: Guided workflows for common incident types (e.g., phishing, malware).
5.	Real-Time Dashboard: Display active incidents, status, and key metrics.
6.	Notification System: Alerts and notifications for new incidents and updates.
7.	Reporting and Analytics: Generate reports on incident trends, response times, etc.
8.	User Management: Role-based access control for different user types.
